<title>AUSTRALIA: OROTON SEES 1996/97 OPERATING LOSS.</title>
<headline>OROTON SEES 1996/97 OPERATING LOSS.</headline>
<dateline>SYDNEY 1997-08-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Luxury goods and clothing retailer Oroton International Ltd said on Friday that it expected to report an operating loss after abnormal items for the year ended July 31.</p>
<p>Australian trading conditions continued to be very depressed with no signs of improvement since it last reported, it said.</p>
<p>The 1996/97 year had been extended to 13 months and the latest results would be released in early October.</p>
<p>Oroton reported an operating loss before abnormal items of A$1.36 million in 1995/96.</p>
<p>-- Sydney Newsroom 61-2 9373-1800</p>
